 Reinforcing its determination to improve the lot of the girl child in Nigeria, members of the board of trustees of the Ajesola Solarin Majekodumi Foundation, ASMAF rose from a closed door meeting with which to usher in the 10th anniversary activities of the non-governmental organization, Friday. Presiding, Emeritus professor Soga Sofola said the team was driven all the time- organizing meetings, looking at programs and implementing policies with a view to actualizing the aim of the Foundation, which is to award scholarships to needy female students pursuing professional courses. Continue reading Support girl child education, trustees tell Nigerians as ASMAF clocks 10 at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard